<p>Twice a year, objects Hawaii lose their shadows as the sun passes directly overhead.</p>
<p>A &#8220;zero shadow day&#8221; occurs biannually between the Tropics of Cancer and Capricorn, arriving at each location when the sun&#8217;s declination equals its latitude.</p>
